HEADWORD: Phonometer
<hw>Pho*nom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Phono-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>An instrument for measuring sounds, as to their intensity, or the
frequency of the vibrations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

